<item>
            <title>[LU-2347] lustre client sometimes reports wrong file size</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2347</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since a few days - possibly due to an update of the Linux kernel to version 2.6.32-279.11.1.el6 - we get reports from users that an &quot;ls -l&quot; command&lt;br/&gt;
reports the wrong (sometimes zero) file size. The behaviour is more or less&lt;br/&gt;
the same that was described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-338&quot; title=&quot;Lustre client reports wrong file size (zero, or too small) on first stat&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-338&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-338&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. We have meanwhile upgraded to &lt;br/&gt;
kernel version 2.6.32-279.14.1.el6.x86_64. The problem still persists.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Client: Lustre 1.8.8, Scientific Linux 6.3, Kernel 2.6.32-279.14.1.el6.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
Server: Lustre-1.8.5, RHEL 5.6, Kernel 2.6.18-194.17.1.el5_lustre.1.8.5</environment>
        <key id="16707">LU-2347</key>
